caption.body: Hollywood costumer Jean Louis came to United with a vision to clothe United’s 4,500 female cabin crewmembers in the latest fashions. His simple and elegant A-line skimmer dress of double-knit  wool came in four combinations of the colors named “Hawaiian Sunset,” “Maliblue,” and “Miami Sands.” See these uniforms on display in "#FashionInFlight: A History of Arline Uniform Design", pre-security, in the International Terminal. http://bit.ly/fashioninflight
